Distribution and habitat. The species occurs in a mountainous region of the western Rif mountains between 719 and 1006 m above sea level ( Fig. 13 ). The climate of the region is Mediterranean type (Csa in Köppen-Geiger classification;
Peel et al. 2007
) with an average annual temperature between 14.5–16.6° C and an average annual precipitation of 906–1052 mm . This climate is classified as humid (aridity index ranging between 0.67 and 0.89) based on UNEP (1997). The species inhabits temporary ponds in areas of cleared forest, mainly composed by cork oaks (
Quercus suber
L.).
